cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper is about creating a virtual library of language resources, which involves aspects of natural language processing (NLP) and digital libraries. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of the Dublin Core Element Set and the OAI Protocol, which are commonly used in digital libraries, suggesting that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the need for precision in community-specific aspects of resource description, which could involve information retrieval (IR) techniques, making cs.IR a possible sub-category. The implementation of Vida and Viser involves developing software, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
